esumed social status tied into a hierarchy of schools and institutions, universities, banks and finance houses. The book explores arguments about what sort of city Edinburgh should be and what it should look like. It examines planning controversies, from post-war developments through various ‘holes in the ground’ up to and including The Trams controversy. Studying Edinburgh lets us draw lessons about cities in general, and their roles in the modern world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aScottish Studies. 7aARCHITECTURE / History / Contemporary (1945-).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2023z9783111318097oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107803900 cprintz978147449830240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147449832640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474498326423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474498326/original  a978-3-11-078039-0  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-131903-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DADb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023